	<text xml:lang="la">
		<body>
			<div>
				<p>
					<s n="1" xml:lang="la">S[alutem] d[ico].</s>
				</p>
				<p>
					<s n="2" xml:lang="la">Scribunt <placeName ref="l18">Augusta</placeName> 28. septembris <persName ref="p8282">Maximilianum</persName> suis <placeName ref="l850">Austriacis</placeName> permisisse refomationem iuxta confessionem <placeName ref="l18">Augustanam</placeName> ideoque <persName ref="p4183">Iacobum Andreae</persName> vocari et nescio quos alios Lutheranos, ut faciant proselytos etc.</s>
					<s n="3" xml:lang="la">Non desinit <persName ref="p4183">Iacobus Andreae</persName>, Architae<note type="misc">vgl. Anm. zu Brief v. 30. Sept. 1544</note> crepitaculum, editis sermonibus Germanicis vellicare Zvinglianos etc.</s>
					<s n="4" xml:lang="la">Pergit et <persName ref="p18233">Illyricus</persName> sui esse similis.</s>
					<s n="5" xml:lang="la">Et ne nimis bona sit inter fratres consensio, venit <placeName ref="l210">Heydelbergam</placeName> Anglus quidam <persName ref="p3979">Wyterus</persName><note xml:id="fn1" type="footnote" n="1"><persName ref="p3979">George Wither</persName>/Withers.</note>, qui ibi (permittentibus ipsis) de excommunicatione disputavit, id est semina sparsit maximorum dissidiorum.</s>
					<s n="6" xml:lang="la">Putasne prudentiam esse, in tanta omnium rerum perturbatione lites et rixas excitare?</s>
					<s n="7" xml:lang="la">Admoneor a fidis per literas, mihi diligenter caveam; esse enim, qui in necem meam conspirarint.</s>
					<s n="8" xml:lang="la">Scio autem me et vitam meam satis tutam esse in dei manibus; cupio insuper modis omnibus dissolvi et esse cum Christo,<note xml:id="fn2" type="footnote" n="2">Vgl. <cit type="bible"><ref>Phil 1, 23</ref></cit>.</note> servatore nostro, ut hic per dei gratiam nihil mihi metuam.</s>
				</p>
				<p>
					<note type="address">[Ohne Adresse.<note xml:id="fna" type="footnote" n="a"><hi>Datum, Unterschrift und Adresse wurden vom Abschreiber durch einen Vermerk am Briefanfang ersetzt:</hi> Idem eidem. <placeName ref="l587">Tiguro</placeName> Bernam. 10. octobris 1568.</note>]</note>
				</p>
			</div>
